        <h2>Where Your Money Goes: The Five Programs</h2>
        <p>Your donation directly funds Arizona's only directly impacted justice organization. A gift of <strong>$50</strong> provides art supplies for a month of <strong>ARTS in Prison & Think Motion</strong> inside Perryville. <strong>$100</strong> trains three returning citizens in overdose response through our <strong>Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention</strong> program. <strong>$250</strong> covers a stipend for one participant in <strong>Core Civics & Advocacy Training</strong>, ensuring economic barriers don't silence directly impacted voices.</p>
        <p><strong>$500</strong> funds a single prison oversight inspection by our <strong>Independent Prison Oversight</strong> team, including travel to remote facilities like ASPC-Winslow, staff time, and report publication. These inspections expose medical neglect and prevent retaliation. <strong>$1,000</strong> supports a month of direct lobbying for our <strong>Criminal Legal System Reform</strong> program, covering policy research that led to SB 1507 and probation reform efforts.</p>
        <p>We maintain an 85% program-to-administration cost ratio. That means 85 cents of every dollar goes directly to programs, not overhead. We publish quarterly financial reports showing exactly how funds are spent, because transparency starts with us.</p>
